name: Grab It & Stab It
description: There was an ambulance call early this summer: male, horseback rider, broken femur (the huge bone of the upper leg). He did not break his leg because he fell off the horse, nor was he kicked by the horse. He broke his femur (the strongest straight bone in the body) when he was dismounting - and while his horse was standing perfectly still. His chaps caught on an elk antler he had found earlier that day and had tied to his saddle, and the point snapped his leg bone in two. It takes a LOT of force to break a femur. The antler did not break. This self defense tool looks like a simple decoration on a bedside table, coffee table, desk, or in the car. However, if you are threatened by someone and you grab it and stab it, it will HURT. This point causes extraordinary pain. Pain, plus the element of surprise, can buy a potential victim a tiny slice of time in which to make their next move: to run like hell, to grab your gun, whatever the situation might dictate in the moment. I took one of these to the mountain this summer. Last summer, when I was being stalked, I had one in my back pocket at all times. It is a gorgeous, simple, natural tool for self defense. It works like a weapon but doesn't look like a weapon. It fits well in a woman's hand, and has enough texture to keep a good grip, even if your hands are sweaty. Try it gently on yourself when you get yours in the mail ~ you'll see how little pressure it takes for this thing to cause pain, and how much pain can be quickly inflicted if you grab it & stab it. Click the second and third thumbnails (and then the images themselves to enlarge even more) for labeled photos which corresponds to antler selection below. Naturally shed elk antler. Carefully selected for straightness and strength. 6 to 7.5 inches long. {legal blah blah}: this is not a toy. this is a self defense tool. using this tool does not guarantee physical safety or emotional well-being. but I hope it adds to your physical and emotional strength. ~~~ shipping: $4.50 with another: $1.50 as always, if cumulative shipping charges exceed actual shipping costs, you will receive a refund via Paypal.

THE ANTLER YOU RECEIVE WILL BE SIMILAR TO THE ONE PICTURED HERE. BEST FOR A SMALL DOG (LAPDOG) OR SMALL PUPPY.

Small = 6 to 7 inches long and 1 to 1.5 inches in diameter. 
Mini = 3.5 to 5 inches long and 1/4 to 1/2 inches in diameter.

Images 1 and 2 represent the SMALL chew toys; image 3 represents the MINI chew toys.  

Naturally shed elk antler, a durable chew toy for your favorite pup, or perhaps a paperweight?

Elk grow a new set of antlers each summer, and each spring, they drop naturally. I go out on my horse and sometimes I'm lucky enough to spot one in the sagebrush.

All sawn edges are sanded smooth.

100% Natural
100% Eco-Friendly
100% Cruelty-Free

***Excess shipping costs (which can occur when multiple antlers are purchased at one time) are always refunded after the transaction is complete***

HELPFUL TIPS:

This antler will stay hard & strong if kept indoors. When exposed to direct sunlight, it will, over time, become faded and brittle.

As with all things that enter your dog's mouth, use common sense to prevent this from becoming a choking hazard. In lieu of that, use supervision.

Charlie & Chloe have enjoyed antlers that are new and hard, and also ones that have become brittle enough to break, all to no ill end. But please do what is best for your dog. 


~~~
